- Centralize all errors in src/common/errors/
- Create domain errors: OrderValidationError, InsufficientMarginError, ExchangeDownError, DuplicateOrderError (and others as needed)
- Map domain errors to HTTP status codes in an ExceptionFilter
- Always log stack traces and requestId for traceability

## Domain errors
- New domain errors must be added to `src/common/errors/domain.errors.ts` and mapped in the HTTP exception filter.
- Use a consistent code (e.g. UPPER_SNAKE_CASE) and include a short doc comment.

## Response shape
- REST error responses must include at least: `code`, `message`, `requestId`, `timestamp`.
- Success list responses should be paginated (page, limit, total) where applicable.